            "id": "5f248d26e9f6964260595990",
            "uuid": "e73e3e57-9b83-456d-818f-e67527089a44",
            "title": "Building Wealth Series: The Wisdom of a Landlord. üè†",
            "slug": "wisdomlandlord",
            "html": "<hr><p>I had a conversation with my landlord today (let‚Äôs call him Baba).</p><p>One of the times he lamented on the advent of corruption in Nigeria which led to a question about land ownership during his younger days.</p><p><em>Then the story began‚Ä¶</em></p><p><strong>8,000 NGN.</strong></p><p>Baba bought his parcel of land for <strong>8,000 NGN in 1978</strong>. At that time, the price of a Peugeot was about<strong> 7,000 NGN.</strong><br>He paid in two instalments and finished the ground floor a year later, in 1979. He got married, moved in with his wife, and had four children. All children were born in the house. Today, they are all highly educated‚Ää‚Äî‚Ää1 lawyer, 1 doctor, 1 Engineer, and 1 Political Scientist.</p><p>Currently, they live in different countries of the world; London, the US, and Canada. It‚Äôs a good life, <em>init? </em>Most of the money‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääa huge chunk‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääused in training the children came from the rent collected from tenants‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääof which I became one recently.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/900/1*MPdu_0YiMAiR5VrSyTnlQg.png\" class=\"kg-image\"></figure><h3 id=\"the-future-value-of-a-good-investment\"><strong>The Future Value of a Good Investment</strong></h3><p>Today, despite the pandemic, he has this house to his name, with no concern for food, clothing, or feeding. Today, my lunch was on him üòâ.</p><p>Baba turned 73 in March.</p><p>Yearly, he makes more than <strong>3 million on all 4 tenants</strong>. Need I say more‚Ä¶</p><p>With even more curiosity in me, I asked: ‚ÄúBaba, what price will you sell this house?‚Äù</p><p>For a moment he was silent, calculating I could guess. Hesitatingly, he gave the back of the envelope calculation. What do you think it was?</p><p>Wait for it‚Ä¶‚Ä¶..</p><p><strong>50,000,000 NGN.</strong></p><p>I would say it again! <strong>F-i-f-t-y MILLION</strong> Nigerian Naira.</p><p>Taking a deep breath, I allowed myself to feel this moment and then my calculative instincts kicked in. <br>Fifty million Naira ($136,000)from an Investment of Eight thousand Naira ($22) just 42 years ago.<br>I did a simple Compounded calculation and the value of his 8,000 investment 42 years ago has grown 23.1% every year.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption\"><img src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/900/1*SxWRgJws3Gv7KaDbcNg6ww.png\" class=\"kg-image\"><figcaption>Compounded Calculation of Baba‚Äôs investment</figcaption></figure><blockquote>Principal‚Ää‚Äî‚Ää$22 <br>Time‚Ää‚Äî‚Ää42 Years<br>Future Value‚Ää‚Äî‚Ää$136,000<br>Rate of Compounding‚Ää‚Äî‚Ää23%</blockquote><p>Totalling <em>6,177.8%</em> in the last 42 years.</p><p>Phew üòÖ</p><p>That‚Äôs about the average compounded rate for Warren Buffet Berkshire Hathaway‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääthe top 10 biggest companies in the world‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääin the first 50 years.</p><p>That conversation got me thinking about how we show off on social media today. But at InvestNaira‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääyour wealth-building companion, your net worth is your boast. If there is one more reason we think you should <a href=\"http://INvestNaira.com/signup\" rel=\"noopener\">begin building wealth with us</a>, today, it is from the wisdom of my Landlord, Baba.</p><hr><p>Bolu | InvestNaira<br>Save | Invest | Owe a Home!</p><p>Follow us on all Social Media @<a href=\"https://medium.com/u/2da0e019decd?source=post_page-----46eaf3675659----------------------\" rel=\"noopener\">InvestNaira</a></p>",
