            "title": "3 WFH Habits to Become Financially Independent. üìöü§ë",
            "slug": "wfh-habits",
            "html": "<p>A few things you can do to tweak your wealth during this season. </p><ol><li><strong>Less Social, More Books</strong>.</li></ol><p>Binge ¬†less on social media and more on books - social media especially the picture laden types fill you with a desire to want to acquire, show off and be in the game. But reading good books keep you mentally alert to make the required sacrifices to be financially dependent.<br>A couple of good books to start with are, <br>* ¬†Richest Man in Babylon by George Clarkson, <br>* Rich Dad Poor Dad by Robert Kiyosaki and <br>* The Intelligent investor by Benjamin Graham.</p><p><strong>2. Create Stretch Net-worth Challenges</strong><br>Nothing keeps the brain working like stretching it to reach difficult ¬†goals. You can have yearly net-worth goals broken down to monthly and quarterly marks. For instance - a goal to increase your net-worth by 1,000,000 in year could be broken down to 90,000 monthly challenges and 300,00 quarterly challenges.<br>These would challenge you to look for smart-earned money and push you beyond your comfort zone. </p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption\"><img src=\"https://nairasense.investnaira.com/content/images/2020/07/image.png\" class=\"kg-image\"><figcaption>Staying Wealthy</figcaption></figure><p>3. <strong>Change your circle of friendship<br></strong>Nothing influences us more than our environments. If the five closest friends you talk with everyday talk about the latest iPhone, the <em>fashioniest </em>clothes and the most luxurious places to visit, you are in a leaky finance ship. However, if your five closest friends talk about new product ideas, opportunities to grow Spiritually, Mentally &amp; otherwise, finding purpose in worthy projects and increasing net-worth, then you would be richer, my dear, someday.<br>The company you keep defines the net-worth you have.</p><p>What other WFH do you think would help increase your net-worth? Pls share with us in the comments below.</p><hr><p> </p>",
