            "id": "5e09bbef4bb28512a342c466",
            "uuid": "ae20eb71-a334-48c8-b119-628913c99a39",
            "title": "Dear Jeff Bezos",
            "slug": "jeff-bezos",
            "html": "<h3 id=\"how-jeff-bezos-built-an-empire-with-a-personal-net-worth-189-300-000-000-in-26-years-at-a-return-of-990-900-\">How Jeff Bezos, built an empire with a personal net-worth 189,300,000,000 in 26 years at a return of 990,900%</h3><p>Hey, NairaSense Reader,<br>One quick question for you, though, {{first_name or ‚Äúuser‚Äù}}, how much did your net-worth increase this week?</p><p>Mine? Not really. But our ‚ÄòFather in the Lord‚Äô, <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/billionaires/\" rel=\"noopener\">the Jeff Bezos</a>- henceforth referred as <strong>JB</strong> in this newsletter‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääon Monday was worth 189,300,000,000. Same day, also, he made 13,000,000,000! And that‚Äôs not in Naira! No Sir! It is in Dollars‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäUnited States Dollars. $$$$</p><p>You must have seen the various breakdown of that money rampant on Social Media. So, I wont bore you with cliches.</p><p>However, in order to bring it home to our <em>hush-colleagues</em>, I did a conversion of $13 billion to Naira @ 388/USD. Well, I could not write it, so I took a <em>picsure.</em> <em>See for ya sef!</em></p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://nairasense.investnaira.com/content/images/2020/07/image-3.png\" class=\"kg-image\"></figure><p><em>Nitori Olorun</em>‚Ä¶. Five Trillion, Fort Seven Billion Naira. Only! Forget the 30 billion Geng! Sca-bda-sho-do-doo-do-dru-ya-ka-te-lemaoooo üôÑ</p><blockquote><em>Fortis Fortuna Adiuvat - </em>Fortune Favours the Brave</blockquote><p><strong>TRIVIA</strong></p><p>If HushPuppy‚Äôs supposed heist to do La Casa De Papel for the English Premier league club had gone through, guess what would be required to heist 13 billion USD, what JB made in one day?</p><p>They would would require 130 <em>hushpuppies, hushdogs &amp; hushwolves </em>&amp; their team in Dubai, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KF2tpV0K8JE\" rel=\"noopener\">NCDC &amp; NDDC, EFCC</a><strong> </strong>&amp; co. to heist 100 million USD each.</p><p>That‚Äôs a whole lotta <em>Bella Ciao Ciao Ciao</em> to heist $13 billion in one day! #BoomBoomCiao</p><p>You see why Hard work compounds? Enough of the shortcuts to wealth. Nigeria, build with <a href=\"https://InvestNaira.com/login\" rel=\"noopener\">InvestNaira today!</a></p><p><strong>High Points of Wealth</strong></p><p>To put his wealth in context, I did a little number juggling! Which one below <em>‚Äòscatter brain‚Äô</em>?</p><ul><li>This year, he has made $74 billion . That‚Äôs the total net-worth of Elon Musk‚Äôs- the 6th Richest man‚Ää‚Äî‚Ää49 years of hard-work at SpaceX, Tesla Motors &amp; SolarCity.</li><li>His Net-worth of $189.3 billion makes him, as an Individual the 53rd largest nation in the world by GDP‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäGross Domestic Product.</li><li>That means His Net-worth dwarfs the nations of Qatar ($183.5 billion) and Kazakhastan ($180.1 billion). Man as a nation!</li><li>His net-worth is bigger than every economy in Africa apart from Nigeria ($448 billion), Kenya ($351 billion) &amp; Egypt ($303 billion). #AriwokoniMusic</li><li>According to World Bank, Nigeria‚Äôs GDP is 26th Largest in the world with $448 billion. JB‚Äôs Networth produces effectively 42% of our GDP. He is worth the productivity of<strong> 84.5 million</strong> Nigerians as a share of GDP. You see why Nigerians are going to Canada!</li><li>His wife, McKenzie Bezos, nee Little, whom he started with and gave 25% of his net-worth, is the 13th richest person in the world. Lessons for power women‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääbuild with your man. But, if he messes up‚Ä¶. üòÅ #JustKeepingItReal</li><li>He started Amazon at 31. His wife was 24. So who told you you are late if you start building in your 30s? #ItisNeverLateToBegin</li><li>Amazon started July 1994, 26 years ago, getting $250,000 from His parents and lending their car to travel with his wife to find a place for Amazon! 26 years <em>fa! Where are the Inspire to aspire to re-fire in order to conspire to well‚Ä¶hell fire</em>! <em>#ThunderFireYou</em></li><li>Today, their combined net-worth, himself and wife, Mckenzie Little, is $250,000,000,000. That‚Äôs an average of 46% compounded annually or 999,9000% in Returns. #RetweetThat!</li><li>Amazon, has a market Capitalization of 1.5T USD, which converts to 63% of Africa‚Äôs GDP‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäOur total GDP in Africa is 2.4 trillion with a population of 1.2trillion.</li><li>That makes it 2$ per African. Amazon‚Äôs 840,000 employees can feed 750m Africans in one day! #Lobatan</li><li>JB owns just about 11% of Amazon‚Äôs stock. It is better to have 11% of a Watermelon than to have a 100% of lime. Build with people, dont be greedy!</li></ul><p>Which one impressed you the most? Retweet and tag us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/investnaira\" rel=\"noopener\">@InvestNaira</a></p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card kg-card-hascaption\"><blockquote class=\"instagram-media\" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/CANnWNLj6-v/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" data-instgrm-version=\"12\" style=\" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:658px; min-width:326px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);\"><div style=\"padding:16px;\"> <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/CANnWNLj6-v/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" style=\" background:#FFFFFF; line-height:0; padding:0 0; text-align:center; text-decoration:none; width:100%;\" target=\"_blank\"> <div style=\" display: flex; flex-direction: row; align-items: center;\"> <div style=\"background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 50%; flex-grow: 0; height: 40px; margin-right: 14px; width: 40px;\"></div> <div style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: column; flex-grow: 1; justify-content: center;\"> <div style=\" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; margin-bottom: 6px; width: 100px;\"></div> <div style=\